AB  - The proceedings contain 65 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Materials, Mechatronics and Automation. The topics include: Electrospun porous ZnO nanofibers for glucose biosensors; hyaluronic acid production by genetic modified GRAS strains; investigation of Au plated connector materials in corrosion and sliding environment; effects of water on the morphology of wool scales; digital image technology based simulation for internal components and mechanical behavior of asphalt concrete; effects of ozone treatment on wool morphology and mechanical properties; reconstruction of bottom surface of shoe last based on foot pressure distribution; an investigated of single point incremental forming formability; design of the gas flow integrating instrument; state and input observer design for nonlinear impulsive systems via LMI approach; analysis and realization of critical points on hardware design of FPGA; study of organic solar cells conversion efficiency; design method and parameters matching of electric motors for hybrid construction equipment; a hierarchical scheme for open system environments review; the improvement of passive location algorithm based on time sequence estimation; deducing stream function N-S equation from classic N-S equation and its verification; a new long-term forecast method of wind power; matching pursuit optimization based on quantum genetic algorithm; a method of recognition of human hand and body gestures for task-level learning from demonstration; study on the control of anti-lock braking system simulation based on fuzzy PID control; smart control of DC servo motor based on fussy-PID; heavy-duty car multi-body dynamics simulation and optimization research; multimedia technology used to reduce costs and time; virtual multimedia environment to teach safety procedures in laboratories; recognition of lanes on complex roads based on video image; the study of chopper in the LVRT of direct-drive wind energy generation system; flow measurement and control system in the campus network; the brainwave concentration analysis of direction recognition; research on the value orientation of supply chain partners' adverse selection; brand classification using distributed representation and empirical research on building Shenzhen into a regional logistics economy center.
